This paper is about image processing using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses training and optimization techniques for neural networks, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a lightweight module that is not affected by spatial resolution suggests that the paper may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and multimedia (cs.MM).
